    • Method Detail

      • addWhere

        public final S addWhere​(java.util.function.Function<Q,​javax.jdo.query.BooleanExpression> whereExpressions)
        Adds WHERE-clause to query. The sample below:

        byJDOQuery(QPerson.class) .addWhere(qPerson -> qPerson.name.eq(desiredName))

        It is possible to define several expressions. The sample below demonstrates how define few expressions aggregated by AND-junction:

        byJDOQuery(QPerson.class) .addWhere(qPerson -> qPerson.name.eq(desiredName)) .addWhere(qPerson -> qPerson.age.gt(age))

        Also it is possible to use junctions.
        Parameters:
        whereExpressions - are functions that return a BooleanExpression on the applying.
        Returns:
        self-reference

        The sample below:

      • orderBy

        public S orderBy​(java.util.function.Function<Q,​javax.jdo.query.OrderExpression<?>> orderExpression)
        Adds ORDER BY-clause to query. The sample below:

        byJDOQuery(QPerson.class) .orderBy(qPerson -> qPerson.id.asc()) .orderBy(qPerson -> qPerson.birthDay.asc())

        Parameters:
        orderExpression - is a function that returns a OrderExpression
        Returns:
        self-reference
